com.bigdata.striterator

Interface IChunkConverter<E,F>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The generic type of the source elements.
    F - The generic type of the converted elements.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BulkCompleteConverter, BulkFilterConverter, DistinctFilter

    public interface IChunkConverter<E,F>
    This is a chunk at a time type processor. Elements can be dropped, have their state changed, or have their state replaced by another element, potentially of a different generic type.
    Version:
    $Id: SPOConvertingIterator.java,v 1.6 2008/08/25 17:21:01 thompsonbry Exp $
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

    • Method Detail

      • convert

        F[] convert(IChunkedOrderedIterator<E> src)
        Convert the next chunk of element(s) from the source iterator into target element(s).

        Note: This method will only be invoked if ChunkedConvertingIterator.hasNext() reports true for the source iterator.

        Note: Iterators are single-threaded so the implementation of this method does not need to be thread-safe.

        Parameters:
        src - The source iterator.
        Returns:
        The target chunk (not null, but may be empty).
